article.headline: Kent State 83, Cleveland St. 68
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Jay Youngblood scored 19 points and Nate Gerwig added 11 points and 10 rebounds to lead Kent State to an 83-68 win over Cleveland State on Saturday. The Vikings pulled within 66-57 with 7:58 remaining but Kent State went on a 12-1 run to seal it. Omni Smith made consecutive 3-pointers to start the spurt. Kevin Warzynski had 13 points and DeAndre Haynes finished with 10 points and five rebounds for the Golden Flashes (3-2), who outrebounded Cleveland State 43-31. J'Nathan Bullock led the Vikings (2-2) with 21 points. Bullock connected on 5 of 9 shots from the field and 11-of-20 from the free-throw line. Raheem Moss, who finished with 16 points, made a 3-pointer to tie it at 31 with 3:59 left in the first half. Gerwig then converted a layup to start a 7-0 run for the Golden Flashes. Kent State shot 55 percent from the field in the first half and led 44-35 at the break.
